correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and not schema- or source-aligned. Key issues: (1) Missing processes: The article reports three ALD OS channels (IGO, IZO, IGZO) with supercycle-based growth; only one IGZO process is provided. (2) Non-traceable/assumed values: Many parameters are not in the article but are populated with arbitrary numbers, e.g., pressure (10 mmHg), growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), nucleation period (5 cycles), dosing/purge times (100 ms), flow rates (10/100/500 sccm), uniformity (5%), conformality aspect ratio (10), optical properties (n, band gap), electrical properties (resistivity, carrier density, mobility by Hall), roughness, density, device metrics (μFE=10 cm2/Vs, Vth=0.5 V, SS=120 mV/dec, ION/IOFF=1e8), stability/reproducibility. None are reported in the paper and thus not traceable. (3) Schema violations/inconsistencies: plasmaPower is set to null (should be an object or omitted); processParameters includes a top-level filmThickness that is not defined in properties (additionalProperties=false); thicknessControl structure does not satisfy required ['values','numberofCycles'] at the thicknessControl level (values are nested under growthPerCycle); duplicate filmThickness appears both inside thicknessControl and at processParameters root. (4) Semantic inconsistencies: supercycleDesign counts are 1:1:1 while materialProperties.atomicRatio is 3:2:1, conflicting within the same process; carrier/purging gas set to N2 without support; XPS is cited for composition though the article shows EDX mapping for IGO and does not report XPS for IGZO. (5) Misattribution/units: Carrier density reported as 1e17 C/m3 conflates donor concentration (~1e17 cm−3) mentioned for IGO (not IGZO) and uses an incompatible unit; pressure unit/value likely incorrect (10 mmHg ~ 10 Torr) and not reported. Corrections needed: add separate IGO, IZO, IGZO processes; remove or leave unspecified any parameters not stated in the article (do not fabricate values); align supercycle counts with reported ratios (e.g., 3:2:1 for IGZO) and sequence; omit plasmaPower if TALD; fix schema compliance for thicknessControl and remove undefined filmThickness at processParameters root; ensure all reported values (temperature 250 °C, precursors TEIn/TEGa/DEZ, O3 oxidant, thermal ALD) are correctly captured and traceable to the text.

completeness.rationale: Very incomplete and partly non-compliant. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article (IGO, IZO, and IGZO ALD), but only one process (IGZO) is extracted. Separate structured processes for IGO (In:Ga=3:2), IZO (In:Zn=3:2), and IGZO (In:Ga:Zn=3:2:1) are required. (2) Many parameters are ungrounded or fabricated: reactor pressure (10 mTorr), dosing/purge times (100 ms), flow rates (10/100/500 sccm), growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å), nucleation period (5 cycles), uniformity (5%), conformality AR=10, optical properties (n, band gap, absorption), electrical properties (resistivity, Hall mobility, carrier density), and device metrics (μ_FE=10 cm^2/Vs, V_TH=0.5 V, SS=120 mV/dec, I_ON/I_OFF=1e8), as well as safety/stability/reproducibility assertions are not reported in the article and are thus not traceable. (3) Supercycle design does not reflect the stated composition control; counts are set to 1:1:1 instead of matching the reported IGZO ratio 3:2:1. (4) Several schema issues: plasmaPower is provided as null (should be omitted or be a valid object); thicknessControl structure does not follow the schema (numberofCycles and filmThickness placed under growthPerCycle; required fields at the thicknessControl level not satisfied); duplicate/ambiguous filmThickness entries; filmDensity unit/value not reported and appears unrealistic. (5) Some aligned items are present (thermal ALD at 250 °C, O3 oxidant, alkyl precursors; subcycle sequence starting with InOx), but overall the extraction lacks traceability and completeness. To improve: add distinct processes for IGO, IZO, and IGZO; constrain supercycle counts to reported ratios; remove or leave unspecified any parameters not given in the article; fix schema compliance (omit plasmaPower, correct thicknessControl fields); and populate only traceable values (e.g., method, precursors/O3, 250 °C deposition, device stack, reported thicknesses such as 7.5–8 nm for IGO and down to 5 nm where applicable).
